of the weight functions\nnearly all information is contained in a small subset of the new second-order\nmeasures. The use of a significantly smaller number of redshift bins than 20\nfor the nulling considerably degrades parameter constraints under conservative\nassumptions, emphasizing the need for detailed redshift information.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Apr 2008 01:24:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Oct 2008 17:59:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-10-21"}
